{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HZKg9ifvxybWSoLvnFh5Df","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Rewrite Acceptance Playbook (Spec-Only Phase)\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\t\n5\tProvide a repeatable way to validate spec quality before implementation begins.\n6\t\n7\tCovered specs:\n8\t\n9\t1. `bridge-mode-contract.md`\n10\t2. `agent-triggers-contract.md`\n11\t3. `chicago-mcp-contract.md`\n12\t4. `teammem-contract.md`\n13\t5. `ultraplan-contract.md`\n14\t6. IME acceptance requirements in `acceptance-spec.md` section 5.4\n15\t\n16\t## 1. Spec QA Checklist\n17\t\n18\tFor each contract doc, verify:\n19\t\n20\t1. At least 6 code evidence anchors with file references.\n21\t2. Crate boundary section exists and is consistent with `README.md`.\n22\t3. Service trait section exists with explicit method signatures.\n23\t4. Error taxonomy section exists with policy/runtime distinction where applicable.\n24\t5. Constants classification section exists.\n25\t6. Acceptance test matrix includes contract + integration + CLI/security tests.\n26\t7. If user input is involved, IME scenarios (preedit/commit/delete/cursor width) are explicitly tested.\n27\t\n28\t## 2. Cross-Spec Consistency Checks\n29\t\n30\tRun document review checks:\n31\t\n32\t1. Error naming style is stable (`*Error` enums, deterministic category names).\n33\t2. Gate and entitlement wording is fail-closed by default.\n34\t3. State machines define terminal states and forbidden transitions.\n35\t4. Remote side-effect features include orphan/session cleanup rules.\n36\t5. No policy logic is placed in runtime adapter sections.\n37\t6. Text input behavior does not assume byte-length editing for CJK input.\n38\t\n39\t## 3. Readiness Gates Before Coding\n40\t\n41\tAll must pass:\n42\t\n43\t1. `acceptance-spec.md` reflects all active contract docs.\n44\t2. `spec-iterations.md` status matches actual document completion.\n45\t3. Each contract has explicit P0 acceptance cases.\n46\t4. Open-risk list is recorded and owner assigned.\n47\t5. IME mandatory cases are listed with platform coverage and expected results.\n48\t\n49\t## 4. Output of Spec Review Round\n50\t\n51\tAt the end of each review round, produce:\n52\t\n53\t1. Passed checks count.\n54\t2. Failed checks with owner and due date.\n55\t3. Waivers with expiry date.\n56\t\n57\tThis ensures implementation starts from auditable, testable specifications.\n58\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AmhVkZizi2XSNnQreLfzwh","session_id":"523981ce-25d5-4aed-a492-78dcbb263a10","uuid":"ad11eaf5-0f81-4c9e-a8f9-8d5223c518a0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T14:21:49.240Z"}
