iants\n- `McpCapabilityPolicy` trait: Validates server names and determines capability levels\n- `ComputerUseLifecycle` trait: Three async lifecycle hooks:\n  - `before_tool_call()` - Called before executing a tool\n  - `after_turn_cleanup()` - Called at normal turn end\n  - `on_interrupt_cleanup()` - Called on interrupt/abort\n\n**Error Taxonomy:**\n1. `ReservedServerName` - Hard-rejected reserved names\n2. `FeatureGateDisabled` - Gate not enabled  \n3. `PrivilegedCapabilityDenied` - Policy doesn't allow privileged mode\n4. `TransportError` - MCP protocol transport issue\n5. `InvalidToolPayload` - Malformed tool request/response\n6. `CleanupFailed` - Non-fatal in interrupt path\n\n**Policy Rules:**\n1. Reserved names are hard-rejected before persistence\n2. Privileged computer-use requires both gate + policy pass\n3. Cleanup must run in both normal and interrupt paths\n4. Cleanup failures don't crash main turn path\n\n**Acceptance Matrix:**\n- **Contract tests**: Reserved names rejected, privileged denied without gate, cleanup API called for both exits\n- **Integration tests**: Registration + dispatch happy path, interrupt triggers cleanup once, cleanup exception doesn't poison turns\n- **CLI behavior tests**: `--computer-use-mcp` routes correctly, errors are deterministic, disabled gate gives reason\n\n---\n\n### 2. Test File Patterns Used\n\n**File naming and location:**\n- Acceptance tests: `{feature_name}_acceptance_tests.rs` (e.g., `bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs`)\n- Test modules: Inline in lib.rs via `#[cfg(test)] mod {test_name};`\n- Unit tests: `{feature_name}_tests.rs` or inline `mod tests { ... }` with `#[test]` or `#[tokio::test]`\n\n**Structure pattern from bridge_mode_acceptance_tests.rs:**\n```rust\n/// Feature acceptance tests (US-XXX)\n/// \n/// Covers all scenarios from {contract}.md §8 Acceptance Criteria:\n///   §8.1 Contract tests  – transport and policy layer invariants\n///   §8.2 Integration tests – multi-step lifecycle flows\n///\n/// CLI behaviour tests live in crates/cli/src/cmd/{feature}.rs.\nuse crate::{/* imports */};\nuse std::/* std imports */;\nuse tokio::sync::Mutex;\n\n// ── shared test doubles ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n#[derive(Default)]\nstruct Mock{Dependency} {\n    results: Arc<Mutex<VecDeque<Result<T, E>>>>,\n}\n\nimpl Mock{Dependency} {\n    fn with_{method}(results: Vec<Result<T, E>>) -> Self { ... }\n    fn for_happy_path() -> Self { ... }\n}\n\n#[async_trait::async_trait]\nimpl Trait for Mock{Dependency} { ... }\n\n// ── §8.1 Contract tests ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/// AC: {acceptance criteria}\n/// \n/// Detailed explanation of why this test matters.\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn contract_{scenario_name}() {\n    // Arrange\n    // Act\n    // Assert with detailed messages\n}\n\n// ── §8.2 Integration tests ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn integration_{scenario_name}() { ... }\n```\n\n**Module declaration in lib.rs:**\n```rust\n#[cfg(test)]\nmod bridge_mode_acceptance_tests;\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Key Types and Structs Referenced in Contract\n\n**From crates/mcp-runtime/src/contracts.rs:**\n\n```rust\npub struct McpServerRef {\n    pub name: String,\n    pub computer_use_requested: bool,\n    declared_capabilities: BTreeSet<CapabilityLevel>,\n}\n\npub enum CapabilityLevel {\n    Standard,\n    PrivilegedComputerUse,\n}\n\npub trait McpCapabilityPolicy: Send + Sync {\n    fn validate_server_name(&self, name: &str) -> Result<(), McpPolicyError>;\n    fn capability_level(&self, server: &McpServerRef) -> CapabilityLevel;\n}\n\npub trait ComputerUseLifecycle: Send + Sync {\n    async fn before_tool_call(&self) -> Result<(), McpRuntimeError>;\n    async fn after_turn_cleanup(&self) -> Result<(), McpRuntimeError>;\n    async fn on_interrupt_cleanup(&self) -> Result<(), McpRuntimeError>;\n}\n\npub enum McpPolicyError {\n    ReservedServerName,\n    FeatureGateDisabled,\n    PrivilegedCapabilityDenied,\n    TransportError,\n    InvalidToolPayload,\n    CleanupFailed,\n}\n\npub struct DefaultMcpCapabilityPolicy {\n    reserved_server_names: BTreeSet<String>, // Contains \"computer\"\n    allow_privileged_computer_use: bool,\n}\n\npub fn enforce_capability_policy(\n    policy: &dyn McpCapabilityPolicy,\n    server: &McpServerRef,\n    chicago_mcp_feature_gate: bool,\n) -> Result<CapabilityLevel, McpPolicyError>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Where MCP Code Lives in Codebase\n\n**Crate structure:**\n- `/crates/mcp-runtime/src/` - Core MCP runtime (400 LOC total)\n  - `contracts.rs` - Policy and lifecycle traits (187 LOC with tests)\n  - `client.rs` - JSON-RPC client adapter (140 LOC)\n  - `transport.rs` - Stdio transport implementation (150 LOC)\n  - Tests: Inline with `#[cfg(test)] mod` directives\n\n- `/crates/tools/src/mcp.rs` - MCP tool adapter for discovery and execution\n  - `discover_mcp_tools()` - Launches MCP servers, enforces policy, discovers tools\n  - `McpToolAdapter` - ToolPort implementation for dispatching tool calls\n  - `is_disconnect_error()`, `format_tool_result()` - Helpers\n  - Tests: Inline in same file, 60 LOC\n\n- `/crates/config/src/schema.rs` - Configuration schema\n  - `McpConfig` - Contains `enable_chicago_mcp_feature_gate`, `allow_privileged_computer_use`, servers\n  - `McpServerConfig` - Individual server registration: name, command, args, declared_capabilities, enable_computer_use\n\n- `/crates/application/src/commands/agent_run.rs` - Integration point\n  - `ComputerUseLifecycle` trait (different from mcp-runtime version, wraps it)\n  - Lifecycle hooks called during tool execution loop\n  - Tests: 3 integration tests for lifecycle behavior\n\n- `/crates/bootstrap/tests/spec_governance_gate.rs` - Contract enforcement\n  - Validates required traits exist: `McpCapabilityPolicy`, `ComputerUseLifecycle`\n  - Validates required errors exist: `McpPolicyError`, `McpRuntimeError`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing Acceptance Test Suites (US-036,